text:
In "The Soul After Death", Fr. Seraphim Rose records a case where a "Yamdoot" demon seen by a dying Hindu man seems to scare crows away.

There is little about Yamdoots on Wikipedia, but there is a story recorded about a dying man calling for his son Vishnu as Yamdoots come to...

... take his soul to Hell, but "Vishnudutas" (I assume Hindu angels of sorts) appear and save him. The point being Vishnu's name is so holy even saying it accidentally like him calling for his son is enough to procure his salvation.

What I find striking is how much this story...

... mirrors experiences of UFO alien abductions in America where an abductee's experience immediately ceases and he wakes up or sees the aliens disappear when he says the name "Jesus Christ" even if he does so accidentally as an exclamation and isn't actually a Christian himself.

Old school psychiatrist will tell you the lunatic asylums closed just when they already were starting to get better and most of the abuses were over. Some psychiatric hospital patients just need to be kept in a cage all their life. Anyone with real clinical experience knows this.

Opening the mental asylums is something that's supported by every real psychiatrist but it scares IYI retards who've read the Foucault Wiki page and think they know what they're talking about without ever seeing the guys who throw excrement at the docs and try to rape the nurses.
Happens to the best of us

It's true in the USSR and communist countries there were enormous abuses of the psychiatric system where they put political dissidents in mental hospitals and forcefully medicated them into zombies but they could have (and have) done that anyways without psychiatry as a field too

Having those aggressive mentally ill patients that get hospitalized every month and then discharged back into the wild is a huge danger for hospital staff because they remember the psych nurses' faces and if they run into them on the street they'll attack them. Has happened here.

I guess in a place like LA or Berlin it's less of an issue but in smaller cities it's likely you'll have crazy hallucinating psychopaths out of their mind randomly meet their psychiatrist or the nurse that gave them meds out in town w/ their family. Some people need to be locked.
